{"type":"message","id":"9ab9ed7b","parentId":"a5004093","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:52:52.633Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, found it. Let me read the end of the file to see what was appended in this pulse.","thinkingSignature":"55c33f297285a394f96da2cedeed170ddce2a516b08bf09e46cf8c14011c17d5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_onklt14m4kbq_1","name":"read","arguments":{"offset":1,"limit":50,"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\research\\CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2401,"output":90,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14628,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774371169944}}
{"type":"message","id":"18519ef4","parentId":"9ab9ed7b","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:52:52.641Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_onklt14m4kbq_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# CFI-Weighted Compression: Experiment Results & Synthesis\n## 2026-03-24\n\n---\n\n## What We Ran\n\n**Hypothesis:** CFI-weighted compression (keep tokens where CFI ≥ 0.7 AND frequency < 60) would outperform frequency-only compression on next-pulse prediction.\n\n**Setup:**\n- 200 pulses, chronological order\n- Train: 160 pulses (80%)\n- Test: 40 pulses (20%)\n- Task: Given compressed state of pulse N, predict pulse N+1 content\n\n**Two strategies compared:**\n- **Strategy A (freq-only):** Keep tokens with frequency ≥ 3\n- **Strategy B (CFI-hard):** Keep tokens where CFI ≥ 0.7 AND frequency < 60\n\n---\n\n## Results\n\n| Metric | Strategy A (freq) | Strategy B (CFI) | Winner |\n|--------|-------------------|------------------|--------|\n| Jaccard | 0.1455 | 0.0127 | A |\n| **Precision** | 0.4254 | **0.5653** | **B (+32.9%)** |\n| Recall | **0.1819** | 0.0128 | A |\n| F1 | 0.2527 | 0.0250 | A |\n| Overlap | 203.4 | 14.2 | A |\n| State size | 483 tokens | 25 tokens | smaller |\n\n---\n\n## What the Results Actually Tell Us\n\n### Finding 1: CFI gives +32.9% precision — CONFIRMED\n\nCFI-weighted compression filters noise effectively. Tokens with CFI ≥ 0.7 are genuine causal anchors with high predictive power.\n\n### Finding 2: CFI-hard has catastrophic recall loss — -92.9%\n\nPure CFI ≥ 0.7 is TOO aggressive. The 0.7 threshold discards almost all valid patterns, leaving only 25 tokens in the compressed state.\n\n### Finding 3: The constant-format problem (NEW)\n\nLook at the frequency=160, CFI=1.00 tokens:\n```\nfreq=160 CFI=1.00 | for next instantiation\nfreq=160 CFI=1.00 | pulse\n\n[169 more lines in file. Use offset=51 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774371172639}}
{"type":"message","id":"8843ce0e","parentId":"18519ef4","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:53:00.140Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have enough context. Let me provide the summary.","thinkingSignature":"f3d0048fc369ec44079f37d6e291c76326dbae5fcc01240dcc5649ec09829c27"},{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n## 🧠 Sandbox Pulse Summary — 2026-03-24 12:52 PM\n\n**Git status:** 7 files changed, +318 / -103 lines. Master: `3bbaacc`\n\n### What Happened\n\n1. **CFI Compression Synthesis** (phase 4/5) identified the **constant-format problem** — tokens like `for next instantiation` and `pulse` have CFI=1.0 at freq=160, but they're artifacts, not causal signals. They inflate CFI without being predictive.\n\n2. **Key insight surfaced:** Compression score should be `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` — the hybrid formula filters out constant-format tokens while preserving genuine causal anchors.\n\n3. **Next action queued:** Implement the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment to validate whether this formula correctly distinguishes \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory.\"\n\n### Mutations Applied\n- **APPENDED** to `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md` — added the experiment results showing CFI gives +32.9% precision but catastrophic recall loss (-92.9%), plus the constant-format problem analysis.\n\n### Mutations Proposed (1 pending)\n- Hybrid scoring Python experiment (`2026-03-24 125214.mutation`)\n\n### File Changes\n- `memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 125214.md` (new)\n- `mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 125214.mutation` (new)\n- `mutations/applied/2026-03-24 125117.mutation` (renamed from proposed)"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2980,"output":358,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15475,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774371172642}}
